@startuml
!include ../style.puml

title Hidden Progress Sources Drive Real Execution

participant "Conceptual Tick" as Tick
participant "Coordinator CPU" as CPU
participant "athens Thread" as Thread
participant "NIC" as NIC
participant "Replica Disk" as Disk

Tick -> CPU : tick
CPU -> Thread : advance execution
Thread -> Thread : handle quorum write

Tick -> CPU : tick
CPU -> Thread : advance execution
Thread -> NIC : send replicate to byzantium

Tick -> NIC : tick
NIC -> NIC : deliver packet / DMA ack

Tick -> CPU : tick
CPU -> Thread : advance execution
Thread -> Disk : follower persists write

Tick -> Disk : tick
Disk -> Disk : fsync / controller work

Tick -> NIC : tick
NIC --> Thread : follower ack ready

Tick -> CPU : tick
CPU -> Thread : advance execution
Thread -> Thread : mark quorum reached

note across #E6F3FF
Conceptual model for presentation:
multiple subsystems make progress over time,
and software observes the resulting interleaving.
end note

@enduml
